## 1. Purpose
This policy defines how [COMPANY]'s ISMS documents are authored, reviewed, approved, versioned, published, distributed, and retained, so that workforce members always work from current, approved documents and so that [COMPANY] can demonstrate document governance to assessors. It is the controlling policy for the metadata header and Version History present in every document in the set.

## 2. Scope
Applies to all controlled ISMS documents — policies, procedures, standards, plans, and registers — for systems and processes within the ISMS scope (`isms-scope-statement.md.template`). It covers documents in any form, with [GitHub]-managed Markdown as the system of record.

## 3. Policy
1. Every controlled document **shall** carry the standard metadata header (Document ID, Version, Classification, Owner, Approver, Effective/Reviewed/Next-Review dates, Applies To) and a Version History.
2. Each document **shall** have a single named Owner (content) and a named Approver (authority to make it effective).
3. Documents **shall** be version-controlled in [GitHub]; changes are made via reviewed pull requests, providing inherent change history.
4. A document is in effect only after the Approver signs off and Status is set to APPROVED; drafts are clearly marked DRAFT.
5. Every document **shall** be reviewed at least annually and upon significant change, with the review recorded (Last Reviewed / Next Review and Version History).
6. Approved documents **shall** be distributed/accessible to all affected workforce members, who acknowledge key policies as required.
7. Superseded versions **shall** be retained, not deleted, for the required retention period.
8. Documents and records subject to HIPAA **shall** be retained for at least **six (6) years** from the later of the date of creation or the date last in effect (45 CFR § 164.316(b)(2)).

## 4. Roles & Responsibilities
| Role | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| Document Owner | Authors and maintains the document; initiates annual review. |
| Approver | Reviews and signs off; authorizes the document to take effect. |
| [Security Officer / CISO] | Owns the document-control process and the master document register (`document-register.md.template`). |
| [GitHub] Maintainers | Enforce PR review and protected branches for the policy repo. |
| All Workforce | Use only current approved documents; acknowledge as required. |

See `roles-and-responsibilities.md.template` for full role definitions.

## 5. Document Lifecycle
1. **Author / Revise:** Owner drafts in [GitHub] using `../_TEMPLATE.md.template`; Status = DRAFT.
2. **Review:** subject-matter and, where needed, legal review (e.g., breach/privacy documents).
3. **Approve:** Approver signs off via PR approval / recorded sign-off; Status = APPROVED; Effective Date set.
4. **Publish / Distribute:** merge to the main branch; communicate to affected workforce; collect acknowledgements for key policies.
5. **Maintain:** review at least annually; revise on change.
6. **Supersede / Retire:** mark superseded versions; retain per retention schedule.

## 6. Versioning
- Pre-approval drafts use 0.x (e.g., 0.1, 0.2).
- The first approved version is 1.0.
- Minor edits increment the minor digit (1.1); material changes increment the major (2.0).
- Every change is recorded in the Version History table with date, author, approver, and a description.

## 7. Classification & Handling
Documents are classified per `../asset-data/data-classification-and-handling.md.template` (typically Internal; some, such as breach procedures and the SoA, are Confidential) and handled accordingly.

## 8. Retention Schedule
| Document / Record Type | Minimum Retention |
|---|---|
| ISMS policies & procedures (HIPAA-related) | 6 years from later of creation or last in effect (45 CFR 164.316(b)(2)) |
| Risk assessments, audit reports, management-review minutes | 6 years |
| Training, access-review, and exception records | 6 years |
| Superseded document versions | Retained in [GitHub] history; 6 years minimum |
| [Other records] | [Per legal/contractual requirement] |

## 9. Exceptions
Deviations from this policy (e.g., a document maintained outside [GitHub]) require documented risk acceptance per `exceptions-and-waivers.md.template`, approved by the [Security Officer].

## 10. Compliance, Monitoring & Enforcement
A master document register (`document-register.md.template`, REG-GOV-01) tracks every controlled document, its owner, approval, and review dates; overdue reviews are flagged and tracked as corrective actions (`corrective-action-poam.md.template`). Document governance is verified at internal audit and management review. Working from or distributing uncontrolled/outdated documents is a policy violation handled per `../people/hr-security-policy.md.template`.

